attributes.name: Papaya Ripe
attributes.description:
When Papaya Ripe its skin turns from green to yellow. If properly ripened, it has a mild to fairly sweet flavor and a creamy, butter-like texture. A Ripe Papaya’s flesh melts in your mouth. People say ripe papaya tastes like cantaloupe melon or tropical mango.

Papayas are an excellent source of Vitamin A, Vitamin C, Vitamin B-9, Calories, Carbohydrate, Fiber, Potassium and Sugar.

Health Benefits of Ripe Papaya :

  • Has Powerful Antioxidant Effects
  • Has Anticancer Properties
  • May Improve Heart Health
  • May Fight Inflammation
  • May Improve Digestion
  • Protects Against Skin Damage

attributes.name: Green Guava
attributes.description: The delightful guava fruit is round or oval shaped, around 4-12cm long. The outer skin may be rough & bitter or soft & sweet, depending on the verity. The skin can be thick or thin too. It is usually green when raw and becomes yellow, pink or light-green as it ripens. A ripe guava is soft and yield slightly when pressed. It has a strong and sweet fragrance. Depending on the verity, the flesh is white, red, salmon-colored and flavour too varies from tart to very sweet.

attributes.name: Custard apple
attributes.description:
Nutritional Facts - 

Custard Apple is low in Saturated Fat, and very low in Cholesterol and Sodium. It is a good source of Vitamin B6 and Potassium, and a very good source of Vitamin C

Benefits - 

Custard Apple health benefits include its ability to improve the appearance of the skin, boost hair health, strengthen the immune system, protect the brain, and benefit pregnancy, among others. There are a good number of polyphenolic antioxidants in custard apple, which makes it an ideal solution for people who want to protect themselves against free radical damage. This can help to eliminate the signs of aging, such as wrinkles and age spots, as well as increasing skin elasticity to reduce the signs of aging. There is a very high level of dietary fiber found in custard apple, which can significantly slow down the release of insulin into your body, in response to the intake of sugar. This regulation is perfect for diabetic patients, who need to be mindful of their balance between glucose and insulin at all times. It can help to soothe the pain of arthritis, while also cutting down on inflammation in the gut and cardiovascular system.
